description: Michael Cao is a sophomore at Penn State University and an advocate for computer science education. His duties in HAX include overseeing all internal activities and making sure everything we do goes smoothly and efficiently. Outside of HAX, Michael enjoys competitive robotics - as an alumni of the FIRST Robotics Competition, he has discovered a passion for robotics and computer science. He also enjoys surfing the web, reading, and chatting with his friends on Discord.
